   <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/valint/sherbug5.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Donna</span><hr size=1> <br>Donna:<br><br>I'm so glad you felt the prayers. I had wondered, but wasn't going to ask, so I'm glad also that you shared this with me.<br><br>Losing friends to addictions sometimes adds an element of pain and grief which wouldn't otherwise be there to compound the feelings of loss. We think, &quot;If only s/he this... if only she s/he that...&quot; And so many of those <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> if</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->'s are addiction related. It's hard for us to accept that our friend, in essence, killed him/herself. We often view it as a suicide-type death/loss, which, for many of the survivors, adds length and depth to each phase of the grieving process, especially the anger phase. I know that for myself this is true. If this happens for you, know this is very normal.<br><br>I'm sorry to hear that so many of her high school friends failed to show for her funeral. Some people just don't &quot;do&quot; funerals, others feel it's inappropriate for them to be present because perhaps they hadn't been in touch with the deceased person for a very long time (guilt), others don't attend because it's such a deeply painful reminder of another loss they've experienced, yet others, and this is terrible in my opinion, don't attend because they simply have no compassion for/don't care about the passed person and/or his/her survivors. Each person's reason for not attending is usually deeply private (or unconscionable--sp?).<br><br>Your &quot;job&quot; is to take care of your own grieving process and not worry about why so many of the others failed to show, however, this does not imply that you won't find yourself angry at them for not attending, and this also does not imply that their absense won't be part of <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> your</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> greiving process.<br><br>More than any of this, always remember you have additional members of your support system, right here, at TSL--and I'm pretty certain we'll all do our best to not fail you during this time.<br><br>Please try to keep us abreast on how you're doing --whether you're having a good day, bad, a numb day or an indifferent day. This will help us help you gauge your grieving process, and will, more importantly, help you grieve.<br><br>Though I can't be with you in person, I can/will be with you in spirit and words. It's not the same, I know, but perhaps it'll provide <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> some</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> comfort.<br><br>Thinking of you,<br>Bree <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/udonnajinfl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Donna J in FL</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.gifs.net/animate/spin3d.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Donna Donna<br>Bo Bonna<br>Fe Fi Fo<br>Fonna</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#000000>(1/30/02 1:25:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boondock.com/visionquest/art/fantasy/fant15lg.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/valint/sherbug5.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Donna</span><hr size=1> Bree - it is essential for me to know that I have so many friends.  Your words do, indeed, help.  I am truly blessed in that I have turned my life with a phenominal support system.  <br><br>And yes, I do understand why some people don't attend funerals but still... I have given myself permission to be angry and resentful for just a little while but this too shall pass.  I have a loving and compassionate network of supportive friends and they never tire of listening to me (and vice versa).  <br><br>If anything good could have possibly come out of all this, it is that I now have reconnected with two very dear friends from the past.  We share many fond memories (and some not so fond) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   but we have vowed to stay in touch.  <br><br>Thank you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb.html" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/01/11/26/flamingtext_com.172516368.jpg" border=0 alt="Image by FlamingText.com"></a><br>Image by <a href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb2.html">FlamingText.com</a></BODY></HTML> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub90.ezboard.com/uvaluable.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valuable</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beaner!</span><br>  Posts: 108<br> <font color=#000000>(1/30/02 8:07:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub90.ezboard.com/fachesandpainsfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.actioninternet.net/users/pets/valint/sherbug5.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Donna</span><hr size=1> <br>My heart is hugging your heart. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>--Bree <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=f5fff9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top